<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/741> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #741" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Vell. 2.8.2; cf. Jerome Chr. ad ann. 340, p. 122 Helm; Degrassi 107, 408f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/740> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #740" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This censorship is doubtful (see RE on no. 322), since Velleius may possibly be thinking simply of brothers who were colleagues in the same office and not specifically of the censorship. If a censorship is meant it must date before 339 when a Publilian law made it necessary to elect a plebeian to at least one place. See 339, Dictator." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/689> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #689" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.23.1; Diod. 16.56.1; Act. Tr.; Chr. 354 (Lenas III et Scipione); Fast. Hyd. (Scipione et Lenate II); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 106, 406f. Scipio was kept from command by illness, while Popillius celebrated a triumph for a success over the Gauls (Liv. 7.23-24, and 25.1; and 25.1; Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 540; App. Celt. 2). On Popillius, see Lübker no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/688> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #688" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Popilius, see Act. Tr. on 350. Scipio has the praenomen {Gr} in Diod." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/677> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #677" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The twelfth of a series (Liv. 7.21.2-4)." .
